namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.
namedLocations.name: ZIP Code

transcript.text: Welcome to Entrend Shop.
Today we will see how to create corporate branding or personalize a corporate store.
To create a corporate branding, go to corporate management corporates, then go to a particular corporate, click on action and then personalized store.
In the personalized store, first of all, you have personalization pages.
So in the personalization pages over here first of all you can personalize the login page.
In the to personalize the login page you can use these variables given over here.
You can add the variable for corporate logo, then the login block and the sign up link.
And when you add this and click on save button in the top, the login page will look like this like it is showing the corporate logo in the top.
Then the login details and registration link as well as the other details added are showing over here which are added over here.
So this is how you can personalize the login page.
Then comes the registration page.
So you can also personalize the registration page by adding this variable given in the top, a corporate logo and registration block and click on save button in the top.
So the registration page will look like this, the logo of the corporate in the top and then the sign up form over here.
Then you can also personalize the reset password page.
To personalize the reset password page, just click on this reset password page over here.
Then add the variables of reset password block and the corporate logo over here.
And after adding this block, you click on save button in the top and the reset password page will be personalized like this.
Like you can see the corporate logo in the top and then the reset password details.
So this is how you can personalize the login page, registration page and reset password page.
Then comes the theme configuration.
So under theme configuration, you can configure the theme for the corporate.
So either you can keep as a standard theme, you can see over here, this is the standard theme or you can personalize this theme for the corporate.
Let's say first is the brand color 1, brand color 2, brand color 3, and brand color 4.
So you can select brand colors from here, like I'll select a color from here, like say dark blue, OK?
Now under this?
You can see where this brand color will effect on the storefront.
Like say over here, it shows that top order menu link color will be changed.
OK?
Then the footer menu link color will be changed.
So likewise, by clicking on the question mark, you can know which brand color will effect where in the corporate storefront.
Like I said, let's change one this one color and show you the example.
I have selected the blue color over here.
Now I'll click on save button over here right now you can see the links in the header are of Gray color.
Now if I when I refresh this page, you can see the links have become blue now.
So the brand color I've changed over here the blue.
So now the links are showing blue color.
Then comes the paste body background.
So you can select the paste body background, either you can keep it at default or you can choose a particular color from here.
Like I'll choose a particular color from here as I choose the green color over here and click on save button.
So right now the background is white.
But I as I have chosen over here the green color.
So when I refresh over here, you can see the background color has changed to green.
So you can also choose the page body background by color or you can upload a particular file for that Suppose I select upload file over here and select image, repeat vertical and upload a file.
Suppose I upload this logo file over here and then click on save button.
So when I'll go to storefront and refresh this page, so you can see the logo file is vertically repeated over here as a background.
So you can also select the background file from here and set the paste body background from here.

Or if you in case you make any mistake or you don't want to personalize this part, you can just select standard theme from here again and click on save button and the standard theme will be restored on the storefront like this.
So this is how you can personalize corporate branding or personalize the corporate store.
And the best way to personalize the corporate store or create a corporate branding is to use this custom CSS part.
You can customize the corporate store by edit custom CSS over here.
You can personalize the way you want your corporate store or create a corporate branding through custom CSS.
If you want to view default CSS, you can view default CSS from here.
And you can go to edit custom CSS and edit the custom CSS and customize the corporate store or create personal branding or corporate branding for a corporate store.
Thank you for watching this video.
